# Prompt 1 – Social Media Content Generation
## Version 1 (v1.0)

### Prompt
Write an Instagram post for Flexikitch.

Respond 

**Caption:**

Still paying huge upfront costs for kitchen equipment? 😩

With Flexikitch, you don’t have to.
Get the equipment your café needs now — and pay over time.

✔ No heavy upfront investment
✔ Flexible rent-to-own options
✔ Upgrade as you grow

More control. Less stress. Better business.

Ready to level up your café? ☕
Send us a DM or click the link in bio.

#Flexikitch #CafeOwners #HospitalityBusiness #SmallBusinessAustralia #CafeLife #BusinessGrowth #SmartInvesting


### Change Made
Basic instruction with no context, Generic post with no clear target or CTA

### Observed Effect
Low engagement potential and not aligned with business goals

### Lesson Learned
Prompts must include audience + goal + structure 


## Version 2 (v1.1)

### Prompt
“You are a B2B marketing expert. Write a 100-word Instagram post for Flexikitch targeting cafe owners. Include a hook, 3 benefits (cash flow, flexibility, maintenance), CTA to book consultation, and 5 hashtags.”  

Respond 

Running a café shouldn’t mean draining your cash upfront.

Flexikitch helps you get the equipment you need—without the financial pressure.
✔ Protect your cash flow with simple monthly payments
✔ Stay flexible—upgrade as your café grows
✔ Enjoy peace of mind with maintenance included

Focus on serving great coffee while we handle the rest.

Ready to make smarter moves for your café? Book a quick consultation today.

#Flexikitch #CafeOwners #HospitalityBusiness #CashFlowManagement #CafeGrowth

### Change Made
Added role (B2B strategist) , Added structure (hook, benefits, CTA, hashtags), Added constraints (tone, word limit)

### Observed Effect
High-quality, usable content, Consistent outputs

### Lesson Learned
Structured prompts gives reliable outputs  
